[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was detected in libexif’s [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` function during a fuzzing run of the [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The overflow occurs when copying [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at the very end [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof a heap-allocated buffer, causing an out-of-bounds read.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue type: Heap-based buffer overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmulti-byte read overflow[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m invokes `exif_data_new_from_data`, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich in turn calls into `exif_data_load_data`, `exif_data_load_data_content`, and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfinally `exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A read of [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting exactly at the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow is triggered by `__asan_memcpy` called inside [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` in `libexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m`.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Stack trace shows the flow:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_entry[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data_content[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. exif_data_load_data[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. exif_data_new_from_data[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe fuzzer entry point[0m[1;39m)[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The buffer in question was allocated via `[0m[1;35mmalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m207[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but the code attempts to[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread/copy [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at an offset of [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m, i.e., immediately past the buffer end.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - No bounds check prevents copying past the buffer’s end.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The failure reproducibly occurs on a single input when run [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m times with [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer under AddressSanitizer.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for further investigation:[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` within `libexif/exif-data.c`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe overflow occurs when copying [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes via `memcpy`, reading just past a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation. An attempted patch replaced two separate bounds checks with a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msingle combined check guarding `doff + s > size`. When re-running the fuzzer, the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow repros at the same source location, indicating the patch did not eliminate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe out-of-bounds read.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer invokes `[0m[1;35mexif_data_new_from_data[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which calls [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_entry[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `exif_data_load_data_entry`, an entry offset `doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` and a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength `s` are computed. A subsequent `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdest, data + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` reads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat `data + [0m[1;36m0x24f[0m[39m`, exactly one byte past the [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte buffer.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ASan reports a “heap-buffer-overflow” at `exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213:3[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcopy site[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdetailed shadow-memory context. The heap block spans `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m0180[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. The read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbegins at `[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…024f`.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch replaced two separate checks  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with a unified check:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff + [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms > [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned long[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A single debug log message was used:  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `[0m[32m"Tag data range past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%lu + %lu > %lu[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the combined‐check patch, the fuzzer run still aborts at the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame line in `exif_data_load_data_entry`. The ASan log is essentially identical in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure, indicating the same out-of-bounds read at offset `[0m[1;36m0x24f[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line numbers shifted slightly [0m[1;39m([0m[39mto `exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:211:3[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the heap-overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unaddressed.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The computation of `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe number of bytes to copy[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and its relationship to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`count` and component sizes: confirm that `s` is correctly bounded by both the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory entry and the overall data block.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any implicit assumptions about the minimum header/footer size [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe initial [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and how it interacts with the entry’s data payload.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Branches in `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmight manipulate `offset`, `doff`, or `s`, including TIFF/endianness handling and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtag type fall-throughs.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory allocation size versus maximum allowed `s`: verify that buffers are [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated large enough for all valid EXIF data, and that invalid/corrupt inputs are[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrejected early.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Related code paths for other EXIF entry types in `exif-data.c` to ensure [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muniform bounds checking across all `memcpy` calls.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe overflow arises when a calculated data‐length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and offset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m permit [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma memcpy to read past the end of a heap allocation. A patch was attempted that [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplaces the original size and overflow checks with a guarded [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit multiplication[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand zero check, [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m clamps the copy length to the available buffer, and [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m3[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith a syntax error: “expected expression” at an `else` keyword, indicating a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalformed `if`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`else` structure in the modified code.[0m                               [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m  malloc …  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow … exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213:3[0m[39m in [0m           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ```  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The function computes `s = format_size * components`, determines where the data [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlives [0m[1;39m([0m[39minline vs offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, then checks `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` before calling `memcpy`. The crash shows these checks did not prevent [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreading past the boundary.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibexif[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpahlsink8[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was triggered in [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` when the fuzzer passed a malformed EXIF blob. The [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitial crash stack pointed to `memcpy` copying past the end of an allocated [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer. A patch was applied that:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Switched size computation to [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit to detect integer overflow.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added checks to reject zero or overflowed sizes.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Computed the available bytes in the buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`avail = size - doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and returned [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mearly if the entry started out of bounds.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Truncated the copy length `s` if it exceeded `avail`.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDespite these changes, the same out-of-bounds read at the same source line [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersists, indicating the patch did not prevent the overflow.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWhen running the fuzz target `exif_from_data_fuzzer` on a crafted input, [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reported:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry` at `exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring a `memcpy`.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The read was [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes long at an address immediately after a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Stack trace:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy`[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_entry` → `exif_data_load_data_content` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_new_from_data`[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` entry point.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe buffer region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m was exactly [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes, but [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe code attempted to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting at offset [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m, thus overrunning by [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modified the block around the calculation of `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtotal data length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe subsequent offset checks:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Wrapped the size calculation in a [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit check:  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   unsigned int fmt_size = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   uint64_t tmp_size = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mfmt_size * entry->components;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp_size == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ||[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->components != [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && tmp_size [0m[35m/[0m[39m entry->components != fmt_size[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   s = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mtmp_size;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Kept existing logic for choosing `doff` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minline vs. offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Added a “clamp” block before allocation:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```c[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   size_t avail = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff < size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m : [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mavail == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* log and return *[0m[35m/[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mavail < s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* log truncation *[0m[35m/[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     s = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mavail;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Left the subsequent `entry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` and [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` unchanged.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result of Patch[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRe-running the same fuzz test produced an identical ASan report:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry`, now at line [0m[1;36m219[0m[39m.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The crash still reads [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes past the [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m byte region.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The stack trace and buffer-region details match the original failure.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis confirms that the patch did not eliminate the out-of-bounds access.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo fully understand and resolve this overflow, one should examine:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The logic that computes `offset` and how it relates to the buffer size. If `doff`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan lie just inside the buffer but still lead to an OOB read after truncation, the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclamp logic needs adjustment.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- How `entry->components` and `entry->format` are validated upstream. If malformed [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor extreme values slip through, they may drive incorrect offset decisions.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The layout of the EXIF data structure in memory—particularly how inline data vs. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal data offsets are parsed and whether bounds checks exist around every copy.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Calls in `exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_load_data` that handle [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiple entries in an IFD; one malformed entry may corrupt buffer pointers used [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlater.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy auditing the offset computations and ensuring that every memcpy source pointer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mplus length is strictly inside the allocated region, the root cause can be [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentified and fixed.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
